Description: Rim sherd of East Greek (North Ionian) pottery rosette bowl; interior: glazed with added red band lined in white; exterior: band at top of rim, dot-rosette below; inscription cut on exterior, over rosette.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of the Dioskouroi (Naukratis), Buried in sand under the west wall of Temenos.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXV, no. 682)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.857)
